  "notes": [
    "This paper presents a cross-sectional study evaluating medical treatment approaches for Cushing's disease across nine international Pituitary Tumors Centers of Excellence (PTCOEs).",
    "The study focuses on real-world clinical practice data for medical management of Cushing's disease, including usage rates and control rates of various medications.",
    "Key findings include ketoconazole being the most frequently used medication (26.5% usage rate) with 76% control rate, and overall median control rate of 75% across all medical treatments."
